Subject: [PATCH] feat(news): L4 industrial-transmission expansion + L2 GPU/CPU
 split + L3 carrier-edge + cascade copy upgrade
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0087 closes the three institutional gaps:

GAP 1 — L4 INDUSTRIAL PASS-THROUGH (FULL UNIVERSE)
  Added EPC chain:        PWR (Quanta), MTZ (MasTec), PRIM (Primoris), FLR (Fluor), J (Jacobs)
  Added connectors:       APH (Amphenol), TEL (TE Connectivity)
  Added cooling/thermal:  TT (Trane Technologies)
  Dual-tagged into L4:    GEV / SMNEY / HTHIY / ABBNY (kept in L1 for capture metric)
                          VRT / JCI / CARR (kept in L6 for efficiency metric)
                          with backlog-pass-through rationales
  India L4:               LT.NS (L&T flagship EPC), HCC.NS (heavy civil EPC)

GAP 2 — L2 GPU vs CPU CYCLE SPLIT
  ComputeSubLayer = 'GPU_SUB' | 'CPU_CYCLE' field added to LayerTicker
  L2 GPU substitution:    AMD-GPU / AVGO / MRVL / AMZN / GOOGL / MSFT / AAPL
  L2 CPU cycle:           AMD-EPYC / INTC / ARM / QCOM
  AMD has TWO rows so it surfaces in both sub-clusters with different rationales
  UI in NewsCard + persistent-bottleneck panel renders L2 with two sub-headers:
    'L2A · GPU substitution (in-stack share displacement)'
    'L2B · CPU cycle (GPU scarcity -> CPU attach + AI-PC + perf/watt)'

GAP 3 — L3 CARRIER-EDGE EXPANSION
  Added LUMN (Lumen IP backbone), VZ (5G MEC), T (cell-site / FirstNet)
  Mandatory on NETWORK_BANDWIDTH; LUMN mandatory on COMPUTE/INTERCONNECT

CASCADE COPY UPGRADE
  Rewrote T1-T4 lines for COMPUTE/MEMORY/PACKAGING/INTERCONNECT/NETWORK/COOLING/ENERGY
  to explicitly name the institutional mechanism:
    T1 -> sentiment + lead-time + CPU-attach signals
    T2 -> revenue acceleration in L1/L4 + backlog 18->36mo extension
    T3 -> ASP repricing -> EBITDA margin expansion 300-800bps
    T4 -> EPS rerating cycle on 2-4Q lag
  This is the 'preform -> ASP -> EBITDA' cascade you wrote, surfaced per-node.

INFRASTRUCTURE
  ROSTER_BY_TICKER -> ROSTER_BY_LAYER_TICKER (key=layer:ticker)
  so dual-tagged tickers (GEV in L1 AND L4) resolve to the right rationale
  per target layer when mandatory-injected.

Cache key bumped v32 -> v33.
